Data
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ BalanceOf
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when account is queried
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the balance for that account
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when account is the zero address
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721InvalidOwner
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ OwnerOf
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when token exists
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the owner address
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when token does not exist
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721NonexistentToken
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ GetApproved
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when token does not exist
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721NonexistentToken
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when no account is approved
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the zero address
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when an account is approved
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the approved account
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ IsApprovedForAll
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when operator has not been approved
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when operator has been approved
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true
в””в”Ђв”Ђ TokenURI
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when token exists
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return baseURI concatenated with tokenId
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when token does not exist
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721NonexistentToken

Approve
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Approve
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when token does not exist
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721NonexistentToken
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is not owner, not approved, and not operator
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721InvalidApprover or equivalent
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is owner
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should set approved[tokenId] to spender and emit Approval
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when caller is operator approved for owner
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should set approved[tokenId] to spender and emit Approval
в””в”Ђв”Ђ SetApprovalForAll
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when operator is the zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721InvalidOperator or equivalent
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when operator is a non-zero address
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set isApprovedForAll[owner][operator] to approved
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit ApprovalForAll

Transfer
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ TransferFrom
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when token does not exist
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721NonexistentToken
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when from is not the current owner
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721IncorrectOwner or equivalent
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when to is the zero address
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721InvalidReceiver
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is not owner, not approved, and not operator
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721InsufficientApproval or equivalent
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is owner
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should transfer ownership, update balances, clear approval, and emit Transfer
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is approved for the tokenId
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should transfer ownership, update balances, clear approval, and emit Transfer
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when caller is operator approved for owner
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should transfer ownership, update balances, clear approval, and emit Transfer
в””в”Ђв”Ђ SafeTransferFrom
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when token does not exist
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721NonexistentToken
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when to is an externally owned account
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should transfer ownership, update balances, clear approval, emit Transfer, and not revert
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when to is the zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721InvalidReceiver
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when to is a non-receiver contract
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when to is an ERC721Receiver contract and returns the correct selector
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should transfer ownership, update balances, clear approval, emit Transfer, and not revert
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when to is an ERC721Receiver contract and does not return the correct selector
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert

Burn
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Burn
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when token does not exist
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721NonexistentToken
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is not owner, not approved, and not operator
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721InsufficientApproval or equivalent
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when caller is owner, approved, or operator
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should clear ownership and approval
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement the owner's balance
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit Transfer to the zero address
в””в”Ђв”Ђ BurnBatch (if supported)
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when any token does not exist
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721NonexistentToken
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when all tokens exist and caller is authorized
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should burn all tokens and update balances
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit Transfer events to the zero address for each token

Enumerable
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ TotalSupply
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when queried
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the number of existing tokens
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ TokenOfOwnerByIndex
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when index is out of bounds
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721OutOfBoundsIndex or equivalent
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when index is within bounds
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the tokenId at that index for the owner
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ TokenByIndex
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when index is out of bounds
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721OutOfBoundsIndex or equivalent
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when index is within bounds
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the tokenId at that index in the global list
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ TransferFrom
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when transfer occurs (owner, approved, or operator)
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should update enumeration (owner's token list and global list)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when to is zero address
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721InvalidReceiver
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when token does not exist
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721NonexistentToken
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when to is a contract
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should call onERC721Received and respect return value or revert
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Burn
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when token does not exist
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721NonexistentToken
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is not owner, not approved, and not operator
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC721InsufficientApproval or equivalent
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when caller is owner, approved, or operator
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should update enumeration (remove from owner list and global list) and burn

Metadata
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Name
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when set (via Mod)
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the token collection name
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Symbol
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when set (via Mod)
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the token collection symbol
в””в”Ђв”Ђ TokenURI
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when baseURI is set
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return baseURI concatenated with tokenId for existing tokens
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when baseURI is empty
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return an empty string or documented behavior

ExportSelectors
в””в”Ђв”Ђ for each ERC721 facet (core, enumerable, metadata, etc.)
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return an abi.encodePacked list of that facet's external function selectors in the expected order

